Action.c(4):           <span class="helpful-info">\n
Action.c(4):             <img class="thumbsup" src="https://assets-prod.sumo.prod.webservices.mozgcp.net/st
Action.c(4):     atic/thumbs-up.2cbd5d41625a84a7.svg"/><span class="helpful-count">43%</span> of users vote
Action.c(4):     d this helpful\n
Action.c(4):           </span>\n
Action.c(4):         \n
Action.c(4):       </div>\n
Action.c(4):           \n
Action.c(4):           <section id="doc-content" class="document--content ">\n
Action.c(4):         \n
Action.c(4):           <p>Firefox's <a href="https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Captive_portal">captive portal</a> 
Action.c(4):     detector tests whether the network connection requires you to log in or accept the network
Action.c(4):     's terms before permitting you to use the network.
Action.c(4): Found resource "https://assets-prod.sumo.prod.webservices.mozgcp.net/static/pencil.e33c563f24c4f989.svg" in HTML "https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/captive-portal"  	[MsgId: MMSG-26659]
Action.c(4): Found resource "https://assets-prod.sumo.prod.webservices.mozgcp.net/static/thumbs-up.2cbd5d41625a84a7.svg" in HTML "https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/captive-portal"  	[MsgId: MMSG-26659]
Action.c(4): t=3759ms: 1228-byte response body for "https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/captive-portal" (RelFrameId=1, Internal ID=5)
Action.c(4):      This is most often the case when using a public Wi-Fi hotspot, but it can also be a corpo
Action.c(4):     rate guest network that prompts you to agree to its acceptable use policy. To learn more, 
Action.c(4):     see <a href="https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/networking/captive_portals.html">Capt
Action.c(4):     ive Portal Detection</a> in <em>Firefox Source Docs</em>.\n
Action.c(4):     </p>\n
Action.c(4):     <div id="toc"><h2>Table of Contents</h2><ul><li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#w_captive-por
Action.c(4):     tal-checks"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Captive portal checks</
Action.c(4):     span></a></li><li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#w_what-to-do-after-the-captive-portal-check
Action.c(4):     "><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">What to do after the captive port
Action.c(4):     al check</span></a></li><li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#w_how-captive-portals-work"><span
Action.c(4):      class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">How captive portals work</span></a></li>
Action.c(4):     </ul></div>\n
Action.c(4):     <h1 id="w_captive-portal-checks">Captive portal checks</h1>\n
Action.c(4):     <p>Firefox tests if the connection is a captive portal by regularly connecting to <code>ht
Action.c(4):     tp://detectportal.firefox.com/canonical.html</code>. Firefox will also make connections to
Action.c(4):      this URL to check if your current network supports certain technologies such as IPv6.\n
Action.c(4):     </p>\n
Action.c(4):     <h1 id="w_w
Action.c(4): t=3766ms: 1228-byte response body for "https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/captive-portal" (RelFrameId=1, Internal ID=5)
Action.c(4):     hat-to-do-after-the-captive-portal-check">What to do after the captive portal check</h1>\n
Action.c(4):     <p>If the page was left open by Firefox, you may simply close it.\n
Action.c(4):     </p><p><strong>If this happens frequently, please file a <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla
Action.c(4):     .org/enter_bug.cgi?product=Core&amp;component=Networking&amp;short_desc=Captive+portal+tab
Action.c(4):     +was+left+open&amp;comment=Steps+to+reproduce&amp;blocked=1198508&amp;bug_type=defect">Net
Action.c(4):     working bug</a></strong> and describe your case (requires creating a Bugzilla account).\n
Action.c(4):     </p>\n
Action.c(4):     <h1 id="w_how-captive-portals-work">How captive portals work</h1>\n
Action.c(4):     <p>Most captive portals redirect you to a login page or a page where you must agree to an 
Action.c(4):     <a href="https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Acceptable_use_policy">Acceptable Use Policy (AUP)</a>
Action.c(4):     . Firefox will make automatic connections to detect these redirects and will notify you by
Action.c(4):      indicating that you may need to log into the network. After doing this, the tab should be
Action.c(4):      closed automatically by Firefox. Occasionally, it will be kept around to display a messag
Action.c(4):     e from the network's owners.\n
Action.c(4):     </p>\n
Action.c(4):         \n
Action.c(4):       </section>\n
Action.c(4):     \n
